HEADWORD: Carucage
<hw>Car"u*cage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>carrucagium</ets> (OF. <ets>charuage</ets>.), fr. LL.
<ets>carruca</ets> plow, fr. L. <ets>carruca</ets> coach.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Old Eng. Law.)</fld> <def>A tax on every plow or
plowland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of plowing.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carucate</ent>⟦br⟧
